law.text:
The board may file a petition and proceed as provided in KRS 201.100, whenever it has probable cause to believe that any child under eighteen (18) years of age:
Is abandoned, neglected or cruelly treated by its parents;
Is habitually sent out or permitted to beg in public places or lives by begging;
Associates with persons who tend to corrupt and contaminate him or her;
Is known to be vicious or incorrigible; or
Has parents who are in constant habits of drunkenness or gross debauchery or who are living together in unlawful cohabitation.
